About 10,000 people are expected to attend this year&rsquo;s Madaraka Day celebrations in Nyeri on June 1.Preparations are in top gear at Kabiruini ASK showground where the fete will be held.The preparations are jointly being carried out by the national and county governments.Nyeri County Commissioner Ngumo Karuku said scores of contractors are working to ensure the work is completed on time. President Uhuru Kenyatta (pictured) is expected to preside over the ceremony with DP William Ruto in attendance. Local groups and the police have been practising ahead of the big day.&ldquo;More than 80 per cent of the work is completed. Internal roads have been rehabilitated. I urge the residents to turn up and welcome the President,&rdquo; the county commissioner said. Security has also been improved.